      "content": "I hear how exhausted you are from fighting a war that feels unwinnable, and it is completely understandable that a therapist cannot suddenly bring someone back or fill the silence you are grieving. Your life feels hollow not because you are weak, but because the foundation was built on something that is gone, leaving you to rebuild in a world that no longer fits. While the pain is deep and the weight is crushing, please know that even in this darkness, there are people who want to sit with you in the quiet and help you find a way to carry it, even if that just means finding a small, manageable way to breathe today.",
