      "content": "it's just that \"breathing\" feels like such a small, pointless thing when the entire air in the room is gone. every morning is just another day of being reminded that everything i loved is dead. i feel like i'm just dragging this heavy, broken body through a life that doesn't even belong to me anymore. sometimes i think the only real way to get some peace is to just... stop. to stop the noise and the heaviness altogether. it feels like the only logical option left.",
